operand_ds.description: Destination register, Source register or immediate

source.immediateRange: -256 to 255 (9-bit signed) or 32-bit with AUGS prefix

operand_ds.usage: Standard two-operand format for most arithmetic, logical, and data movement instructions

codingRules.registerRange: R0-R511, or named registers like PA, PB, PTRA, PTRB
codingRules.immediateExtension: Use AUGS prefix for 32-bit immediate values

limitations.immediate: 9-bit signed (-256 to +255) without prefix, 32-bit with AUGS

examples: ADD R0, R1         // Register to register

operand_du.description: Destination register, optional Source register or immediate

source.immediateRange: -256 to 255 (9-bit signed) or 32-bit with AUGS prefix
source.defaultBehavior: Uses destination as source if omitted

operand_du.usage: Single-operand instructions that can optionally take a source parameter

codingRules.defaultSource: When source omitted, instruction uses destination as source

limitations.source: If provided, follows same rules as operand_ds source

examples: NOT R0, R1       // Two operands, R0 = ~R1

operand_ls.description: Immediate or register for both destination and source

destination.immediateRange: -256 to 255 (9-bit signed) or 32-bit with AUGS prefix

source.immediateRange: -256 to 255 (9-bit signed) or 32-bit with AUGS prefix

operand_ls.usage: Instructions that can use immediate values for both operands
examples: WRPIN PA, PB          // Register to register

operand_dsp.description: Destination register, Source with pointer register option

source.immediateRange: -256 to 255 (9-bit signed) or 32-bit with AUGS prefix

operand_dsp.usage: Memory access instructions that can use pointer registers with auto-increment/decrement

codingRules.addressMode: Can use absolute addresses or pointer registers

limitations.destination: Must be register for read operations
limitations.pointerRange: Only PTRA and PTRB available as pointer registers

examples: RDBYTE R0, PTRA++     // Read byte, increment PTRA by 1
RDWORD result, #$1000 // Read word from absolute address
RDLONG data, PTRB--   // Read long, decrement PTRB by 4
RDBYTE R0, R1         // Read from address in R1

operand_bitx.description: Destination register, Source register or immediate (bit operations)

codingRules.destinationModified: Destination register is modified based on bit operation
codingRules.noFlagEffects: These instructions cannot set C or Z flags

limitations.bitRange: Bit positions limited to 0-31 for immediate values
limitations.flagRestriction: Cannot use WC, WZ, or WCZ effect flags

examples: BITL R0, #7      // Set bit 7 of R0 to 0
BITH flags, R1   // Set bit (R1 value) of flags to 1
BITC status, #0  // Set bit 0 of status to C flag
BITRND R0, #15   // Set bit 15 of R0 to random value

operand_jpoll.description: Source register or immediate (jump on poll)

codingRules.relativeAddressing: Branch addresses are relative to current PC
codingRules.eventCondition: Jump occurs based on hardware event status
codingRules.pollTypes: INT, CT1-3, SE1-4, PAT, FBW, XMT, XFI, XRO, XRL, ATN, QMT

limitations.eventSpecific: Each instruction polls specific hardware event

examples: JINT #handler        // Jump to handler if interrupt pending
JCT1 @@timeout       // Jump to timeout if CT1 expired
JSE1 #serial_ready   // Jump if serial event 1 ready
JNCT2 R0            // Jump to address in R0 if CT2 not expired

WC.name: Write Carry
WC.description: Instruction sets/clears the carry flag based on operation result
WC.usage: Arithmetic overflow, shift/rotate bit output, comparison results

WZ.name: Write Zero
WZ.description: Instruction sets/clears the zero flag based on operation result
WZ.usage: Zero result detection, equality comparison, bit testing

WCZ.name: Write Carry and Zero
WCZ.description: Instruction affects both carry and zero flags
WCZ.usage: Full flag status from arithmetic and logical operations

none.name: No Effect Flags
none.description: Instruction cannot affect carry or zero flags
none.usage: Bit manipulation, memory operations, unconditional jumps
